The African National Congress (ANC) secretary-general Ace Magashule speaks to SABC’s Samkele Maseko. Magashule discusses among other issues, the outcome of ANC NEC meeting and allegations of COVID-19 related corruption. Part 1: Magashule on PPEs  Magashule’s sons are listed as directors of two companies, Motheko Projects and Marvel Deeds, which are among the companies that secured contracts with Free State Treasury. Part 2: Ace Magashule on other issues affecting the party  The Presidency on Thursday sets up a committee to probe corruption allegations in procurement. “Government is taking decisive action not only to safeguard COVID-19 funds but also to strengthen our response against the broader problem of corruption in our society,” the Presidency says. 